title: For Sale:  SOLD ! - Whitney Wolverine - Original 1956
postcontent:
SOLD !

This is not an Olympic Arms Wolverine. 	

This is an original Whitney Wolverine pistol manufactured by Whitney Firearm, Inc., New Haven Conn. in Oct. 1956. It is S/N 30,XXX and comes with the original box numbered to the gun and a factory instruction sheet/parts list. The frame is cast from Alcoa #380 aluminum and it does not have “Wolverine” on the right side.

The pistol is in very nice condition. There is a nice contrast between the dark gray main frame and the gloss black barrel shroud. There is very little in the way of storage or handling marks on the finish. The grips are nice and sharp with no edge chipping.

It is excellent mechanically and the bore is bright with no pitting. It’s doubtful if the pistol has ever been fired.

The box is original and not in great condition. The Alcoa Aluminum sticker is still in place on the bottom of the box. The interesting thing about the box is the “Klein’s” stickers. Klein’s was a mail order house in Chicago. Not only did they handle this pistol but they sold Lee Harvey Oswald the Carcano rifle used to assassinate John F. Kennedy.

Buyer pays $30 shipping.

title: For Sale:  1944 German Mauser - Original Third Reich Markings, Great Condition + 1 Box of 8mm ammo
postcontent: Up for sale is a beautifully restored K98 German Mauser. The barrel, the bolt handle, the floor plate, and the stock match, as the pictures show. The striker is numbered and is a mismatch. There are no other numbered visible parts. The bolt body was electro-penciled to match, as the pictures show. The German eagle is present on the left hand side of the receiver, as the picture shows. The metal was professionally reblued with no corner rounding or dished-out holes. The stock was chemically stripped, steamed, and the remaining compressions and gouges were filled with matching epoxy before lightly sanding, staining and finishing. The wood is always flush with the mating steel surfaces and nothing dished out. The restored condition is excellent with no scratches or dings. The bore is excellent -- shinny with no discolorations. Great buy.

title: For Sale:  New Frontier AR (aluminum) with quality parts - LOW ROUND COUNT
postcontent:
Up for sale is a New Frontier Armory (aluminum, not polymer) AR that has been refinished in Coyote Brown. This AR was built with quality parts and I'm only asking for what I have into it. The matched upper and lower lock in very tight, tighter than any AR I've owned. Here is a list of what it has:

- JP Enterprises adjustable gas block (.750 diameter)
- Spikes branded mid length FN 14.5" 5.56 barrel with pinned and welded BCM Mod 1 compensator for legal length.
- Spikes bolt carrier and bolt
- Magpul MOE Mid length hand guard. This was FDE but I dyed it black.
- Larue LT-103 fixed rear sight
- Troy gas block height M4 style tritium folding front sight
- DPMS mid length gas tube, delta ring and barrel nut
- Magpul MIAD grip 
- DPMS LPK
- Phase 5 Tactical winter trigger guard
- Magpul UBR stock
- Voodoo tactical single point bungee sling

I'll even throw in three unused but opened C-Products mags and your choice of either a NIW GenII Windowed PMAG or a GenIII non windowed PMAG. 

I have only put 180 rounds through this rifle. It is very accurate and has an awesome balance to it. I won't be sad if it doesn't sell, just trying to use this as a catalyst to fund other projects. I don't need to sell so no low ball offers please.

The coyote finish on this rifle is somewhat iffy. It's very thick and has a tendency to chip from pins and such moving around. Most that damage is already done though (from take down and such). I bought the upper and lower done this way and am not certain what was used. The finish is still in pretty good shape though. Also, due to the finish being so thick, I had to sand the finish under the Larue rear sight for it to sit flush. I had planned to strip it and have it redone once it got to a point where it started looking ugly. It's far from that point though. It's really not as bad as I make it sound but I like to disclose issues to buyers as I'm not here to push garbage in others laps. Simply trying to fund other projects.


Only trade I'd be interested in is another non-poly lower, complete or stripped(plus cash obviously).

Would prefer a FTF sale. Must be willing to show a valid state issued ID to verify age and residency. If you're from Denver city or county, I cannot include the magazines. Please let me know if you are ahead of time and we'll work on a price without the mags I'm offering.

Feel free to e-mail me via the site with any questions.

Thanks for looking!
